    "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nTwo related bugs prevent `--tp N --ep M --enable-lora --lora-backend triton --moe-runner-backend triton` from running on any MoE model with per-expert LoRA adapters; both reliably crash in the first forward pass with `CUDA error: an illegal memory access was encountered`. This PR fixes both and adds unit coverage.\r\n\r\n### Bug 1 — `LoRAMemoryPool` sizes per-expert buffers for the global expert count\r\n\r\n`FusedMoEWithLoRA` allocates LoRA A/B buffers via `LoRAMemoryPool`, whose per-expert shape was `[num_loras, num_global_experts, ...]`. Under EP, however, `StandardDispatcher` remaps `topk_ids` from global → local IDs *before* the MoE kernel (see `python/sglang/srt/layers/moe/token_dispatcher/standard.py`), so both the base MoE weights and the LoRA delta kernels are indexed with IDs in `[0, num_local_experts)` plus a `-1` sentinel. A LoRA buffer sized `[..., 128, ...]` being indexed with local IDs `[0, 32)` therefore reads the wrong expert's weights (or, combined with bug #2, triggers the illegal access).\r\n\r\n### Bug 2 — `moe_lora_align_block_size` doesn't filter the `-1` sentinel in one branch\r\n\r\n`_count_and_sort_expert_tokens` only rejected `expert_id >= num_experts`:\r\n\r\n```cpp\r\nfor (size_t i = tid; i < numel; i += stride) {\r\n  int32_t expert_id = topk_ids[i];\r\n  if (expert_id >= num_experts) { continue; }      // <-- no `< 0`\r\n  ...\r\n  int32_t rank_post_pad = atomicAdd(\r\n    &cumsum_buffer[(model_offset * (num_experts + 1)) + expert_id], 1);\r\n  sorted_token_ids[max_num_tokens_padded * model_offset + rank_post_pad] = i;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n`-1` passes that guard and produces:\r\n- `atomicAdd(&cumsum_buffer[model_offset * (num_experts+1) + (-1)], 1)` — OOB write (negative stride), and\r\n- `sorted_token_ids[offset + rank_post_pad]` with a garbage `rank_post_pad`.\r\n\r\nBoth sibling call sites in the same file already guard `expert_id < 0 || expert_id >= num_experts`. This PR makes the third call site consistent.\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- **`python/sglang/srt/lora/mem_pool.py`**\r\n  - Capture `(moe_ep_size, moe_ep_rank)` and `moe_use_local_expert_ids` at pool init. The latter is `True` iff `moe_ep_size > 1` **and** the active runner remaps to local IDs (Triton/DeepGEMM/Marlin) — the check is skipped for runners that keep global IDs (FlashInfer CUTLASS / CuteDSL / TRTLLM-routed), so their buffers stay globally-keyed.\r\n  - Size per-expert LoRA buffers by `num_local_experts` (`get_lora_A_shape` / `get_lora_B_shape`).\r\n  - Route all four per-expert load paths in `load_lora_weight_to_buffer` through a new `_iter_local_expert_weights(weights)` helper that filters and remaps global → local expert IDs for both `dict` and 3D-tensor inputs, then zeros unowned/unloaded slots.\r\n  - No-op for pure TP and for runners that keep global IDs — verified by the TP-only LoRA unit tests, which still pass unchanged.\r\n\r\n- **`python/sglang/jit_kernel/csrc/lora/moe_lora_align_kernel.cu`**\r\n  - Add `expert_id < 0` to the guard in `_count_and_sort_expert_tokens`, matching the two other call sites; adds a comment explaining the sentinel contract with `StandardDispatcher`.\r\n\r\n- **`test/registered/unit/lora/test_mem_pool_ep_unit.py`** (new, 22 cases, hermetic CPU-only)\r\n  - `_get_num_experts` covering `num_experts`, `num_local_experts`, `n_routed_experts`, and fallbacks.\r\n  - `_get_num_local_experts` under no-EP / EP=1 / EP=4 and uneven splits.\r\n  - `_global_to_local_expert_id` ownership filter.\r\n  - `_iter_local_expert_weights` for dict and 3D-tensor inputs, with correct remapping under EP.\r\n  - `LoRAMemoryPool.__init__` EP-context capture for no-EP, Triton+EP, and FlashInfer+EP.\r\n\r\n## Compatibility\r\n\r\n- **Pure TP (any `--tp`, no `--ep`)**: `moe_ep_size == 1` → `moe_use_local_expert_ids == False` → buffers and iteration are identical to pre-fix behavior. Verified end-to-end with `--tp 2` + LoRA.\r\n- **Pure EP**: per-rank buffers and remapping via `_iter_local_expert_weights`.\r\n- **Mixed TP + EP**: same as pure EP — TP slicing already happened when the base model loaded; the LoRA fix only affects the expert dimension.\r\n- **FlashInfer CUTLASS / CuteDSL / TRTLLM-routed**: `_moe_runner_keeps_global_expert_ids()` returns `True`, `moe_use_local_expert_ids` stays `False` → buffers stay globally-keyed, matching what those runners expect.\r\n- **Non-LoRA paths**: untouched.\r\n\r\n## Test plan\r\n\r\n- [x] `pytest test/registered/unit/lora/test_mem_pool_ep_unit.py` — 22 passed.\r\n- [x] `pre-commit run --files ...`\r\n- [x] End-to-end regression that originally reproduced the crash:\r\n  ```bash\r\n  python -m sglang.launch_server \\\r\n    --model-path Qwen3-VL-30B-A3B-Instruct-FP8 \\\r\n    --tp 4 --ep 4 \\\r\n    --enable-lora --max-loras-per-batch 1 --max-lora-rank 32 \\\r\n    --lora-target-modules all --lora-paths lora_alpha=<per-expert adapter> \\\r\n    --lora-backend triton --moe-runner-backend triton\r\n  # curl /v1/completions -> before: CUDA illegal memory access in first forward\r\n  #                        after : returns a completion successfully\r\n  ```\r\n- [x] `--tp 4 --ep 4` base (no `--enable-lora`) still works.\r\n- [x] `--tp 2` (no EP) + LoRA still works (regression for the non-EP path).",
    "created_at": "2026-04-19T18:44:51Z",
